📊 **SAP Supplier Evaluation: Driving Smarter Procurement Decisions**

Supplier Evaluation in SAP S/4HANA helps organizations assess and monitor supplier performance using data from Materials Management (MM), Logistics Information System (LIS - S013), and Quality Management (QM).

🔹 **Key Evaluation Criteria:**
• Price 💰
• Quality ⭐
• Delivery 🚚
• Service 🤝
• Invoice Verification 📄
• Sustainability 🌱

🔹 **How it works:**
✅ Suppliers are scored using automatic, semiautomatic, and manual criteria.
✅ Weighting factors prioritize what's most important to the business.
✅ Performance is evaluated through metrics such as price competitiveness, quality inspections, on-time delivery, quantity reliability, and audit results.
✅ Supplier evaluations support better sourcing decisions, supplier monitoring, and continuous improvement initiatives.

🔹 **Key SAP Transactions:**
• ME61 – Maintain Supplier Evaluation
• ME63 – Automatic Re-evaluation
• ME6F – Print Evaluation Sheet

A well-designed supplier evaluation process enables organizations to make data-driven procurement decisions, strengthen supplier relationships, reduce risks, and optimize supply chain performance.

